title: The chancellor is safe, for now.
on-arrival: papen_goal = "Push for his own reappointment"; meissner_goal = "Reconcile Schleicher and Hindenburg"; oskar_goal = "Push for Papen's reappointment"; papen_strength -= 1; hindenburg_schleicher_r += 1

Papen's constant nagging remains a thorn in Schleicher's side, especially given that the former chancellor lives just meters from the President's residence—and with Oskar von Hindenburg continuing to influence his father.

Meissner, however, has come to a realization: Schleicher is here to stay. He is not driven by ideology—having served under Ebert beforehand; he was simply trying to do what he believed was best for the nation—an aim that now means supporting Schleicher and his policies.